(r\sin t,r\cos t, ct)
c,r
\kappa,\tau
 \kappa = \frac{r}{r^2+c^2}\\ \tau = \frac{c}{r^2+c^2} 
 \theta=\arctan\left(\frac{c}{r}\right)\\ \rho=\sqrt{c^2+r^2} 
 \kappa = \frac{\cos\theta}{\rho}\\ \tau = \frac{\sin\theta}{\rho} 
 \theta=\arctan\left(\frac{\tau}{\kappa}\right)\\ \rho=\frac{1}{\sqrt{\tau^2+\kappa^2}} 
 \kappa = \frac{r}{r^2+c^2}\\ \tau = \frac{c}{r^2+c^2} 
 \frac{\kappa}{\tau}=\frac{r}{c} 
 \kappa^2+\tau^2=\frac{1}{(r^2+c^2)^2} 
 r=c\frac{\kappa}{\tau}\\ r^2+c^2=\frac1{\sqrt{\kappa^2+\tau^2}} 
